FIGURE 2 | Seasonal aboveground biomass (BM; A), nitrogen (N; B), phosphorus (P; C), and potassium (K; D) accumulation and partitioning in stalks,
dry leaves, and tops of sugarcane during a ﬁrst ratoon growing season, in overall for all three site-years located in the Southeast region of Brazil.
Arrows indicate when sugarcane BM and nutrient accumulation achieved 50% relative to its ﬁnal content at harvest time.

FIGURE 3 | Relationships between sugarcane yield versus aboveground nutrient content for N (A), P (B), and K (C); and versus stalk nutrient content
(nutrient removal) for N (D), P (E), and K (F). Each data point represents an individual ﬁeld plot at sugarcane harvest of a ﬁrst ratoon growing season for three
site-years (n = 102). Red symbols were gathered from previously published documents (Shukla et al., 2009; Oliveira et al., 2010; Schultz et al., 2010; n = 27). ∗∗∗,
∗∗, and NS: p ≤ 0.001, p ≤ 0.01, and non-signiﬁcant (p > 0.05), respectively.
